==Old English==
===Etymology===
From Germanic: cognate with Old Frisian [[balu]], Old Saxon [[balu]], Old High German [[balo]], Old Norse {{Latinx|[[bǫl]]}}, Gothic [[𐌱𐌰𐌻𐍅𐌴𐌹𐌽𐍃]].

===Pronunciation===
{{IPA|/ˈbæalo/}}

===Noun===
'''bealo''' {{n}} (''gen'' '''[[bealwes]]''')
# ''(Poetic)''  [[harm]], [[evil]], [[malice]]
#:''Ne ondræde ic ðinra wita bealo'': I do not dread the evil of your torments.  (''Codex Exoniensis'')

====Descendents====
*English [[bale]]

===Alternative forms===
*[[bealu]]
*[[balu]]

